        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Please, let me know if I'm wrong but I think that \"$options\" passed to \"Zend_Translate\" constructor are not automatically set to the adapter object. I mean, they're used to instanciate the adapter BUT its \"_options\" property is not set with this value. So if I want to use some particular options in a new translate object (and its adapter) I must call both methods (constructor and setOptions) with the \"$options\" array. Example:\n\n{code} \n$options = array('separator' => '|');\n$this->_translate = new Zend_Translate($this->transl_adapter, $file, $language, $options);\n$this->_translate->setOptions($options);     \/\/ $options \u00bfagain?\n{code} \n"
        },
