        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19477",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You are wrong. :-)\n\nWhy should a factory class itself set a private property of another class ?\nZend_Translate creates a new adapter passing the options parameter to the constructor of the created class.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-28T10:39:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-28T10:39:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19479",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=marcis",
                        "name": "marcis",
                        "displayName": "Marcos Gil Fuertes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well, maybe I didn't explain properly: it should be the \"Zend_Translate_Adapter\" constructor who saves the \"$options\" array it receives.\n\nLook at the code I wrote: don't you think it's stupid to call \"setOptions\" if you just created the object with the same \"$options\"?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=marcis",
                        "name": "marcis",
                        "displayName": "Marcos Gil Fuertes",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-28T10:53:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-28T10:53:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19483",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well, maybe you wrote \"Zend_Translate\" and also your example states \"Zend_Translate\" ? ;-) ;-)\nBtw: Quite confusing, as noone knows what $this->transl_adapter is...\n\nI'll have a look at it",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
